name: integer_i16_minimum
description: |
  This is the minimum i16 value, -32768. Its positive magnitude, 32768, is not
  representable as an i16, so unary negation and absolute-value operations may
  overflow, trap, wrap, or require a wider result type. Dividing it by -1 also
  has the mathematically correct but unrepresentable quotient 32768, while
  subtracting 1 crosses the lower arithmetic boundary.
format: hex
decode-as: i16
pair:
  - with: negative-one.input
    hint: tricky
  - with: one.input
    hint: tricky
  - with: ../u16/high-bit.input
    hint: tricky
tags:
  - "integer"
  - "signed-integer"
  - "i16"
  - "minimum"
  - "boundary"
  - "overflow"
  - "underflow"
  - "absolute-value"
  - "two's-complement"
---
00 80   # -32768
